    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2002 BMW M3, a quintessential E46 chassis featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This power unit utilizes six individual throttle bodies and double VANOS variable valve timing to produce a linear power band up to an 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered through a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission to a limited-slip Variable M Differential. This example has undergone essential preventative maintenance, including rear subframe reinforcement and rod bearing replacement, ensuring structural and internal longevity. The suspension benefits from refreshed OEM bushings, maintaining the sharp turn-in and communicative feedback these cars are known for. A mechanically honest driver\u2019s car for the enthusiast who values performance over garage-queen status.",
